# Shell Commands Outside Sandbox

When running the following shell commands, ALWAYS use the `required_permissions: ["all"]` parameter with the Shell tool to run OUTSIDE the sandbox. DO NOT ASK for permission - just do it.

## Commands

- `cd` - Change directory (needed for navigation)
- `tail` - Display file contents from the end
- `head` - Display file contents from the beginning
- `grep` - Search patterns in files
- `./gradlew` - ALWAYS run gradle commands outside sandbox

## Examples

```kotlin
// Changing directory (needs all permissions)
Shell(
    command = "cd /path/to/directory",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
)

// Using tail to read file (needs all permissions)
Shell(
    command = "tail -n 50 /path/to/file",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
)

// Using head to read file (needs all permissions)
Shell(
    command = "head -n 50 /path/to/file",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
)

// Using grep to search (needs all permissions)
Shell(
    command = "grep -r \"pattern\" /path/to/directory",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
)

// Running gradle commands (ALWAYS outside sandbox)
Shell(
    command = "./gradlew assembleDebug",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
    block_until_ms: 600000,
)
```

## Why This Is Needed

The sandbox restricts process spawning and certain shell operations. These commonly-used commands may require permissions outside the sandbox to function properly. Without `required_permissions: ["all"]`, commands may fail with "Operation not permitted" errors.
